SIMPLE: happen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Happen
<hw>Hap"pen</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧p"p'n)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Happened</conjf>
<pr>(-p'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Happening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>happenen</ets>,
<ets>hapnen</ets>. See <er>Hap</er> to happen.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To come by chance; to come without previous expectation; to fall
out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There shall no evil <qex>happen</qex> to the just.</q>
<rj><qau>Prov. xii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take place; to occur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All these things which had <qex>happened</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Luke
xxiv. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To happen on</b></col>, <cd>to meet with; to fall or
light upon.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧I have <xex>happened on</xex> some other
accounts.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Graunt.</au> -- <col><b>To happen in</b></col>,
<cd>to make a casual call.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>happening</ent>⟦br⟧
